post_text:
Tonight The DOGS of Redtail Ridge invaded Feed My Starving Children in Eagan!
Our kiddos learned an important lesson tonight, don't take for granted the food that is in their fridge or pantry, many kids just like them in parts of the world are not as fortunate as we are. Also it is important to volunteer, help others and how much you can accomplish with teamwork!
The Big DOGS and little DOGS packed 28.5 boxes, or 1,026 bags of food in 2hrs!
Great job!

post_text:
We would like to give a BIG thank you to the Redtail Ridge Community! We had our best turnout yet for the pancake breakfast yesterday. Without the support of or school staff, PTC and the families of this school we would not be able to do what we do for our kiddos!
Even after the generous gifts to the students for the Read-A-Thon in February, you all still came out to support us and we thank you!
The children at Redtail are lucky to live in such a caring and giving community.
Stay tuned.... Big things yet to come from the DOGS of Redtail Ridge!
Once again thank you all for your support!

It's was a long weekend of work for the DOGS! Once again adding to the educational experience our kids get when they attend Redtail Ridge.
The kindergarten outdoor classroom is nearly complete. A HUGE thank you to the dedicated dads in this community who spent most of their weekend giving back to the school the best way we know how, with our hands and power tools!

Learning happens everywhere, not just in a classroom!

Enjoy!

post_text:
We could use additional volunteers for tonight's event at Redtail. The response has been fantastic and attendance is beyond our estimation. We will be grilling 400+ hot dogs which is the most we have ever done, awesome!

If you can help out please stop by, we will be setting up outside of the cafeteria by the playground equipment. DOGS will be getting ready at the school right when it lets out for the day, some as early as 4pm to start grilling.

Thank you.

post_text:
Good time for a greater cause!
Awesome job DOGS, showing our little ones that giving is better than receiving!

In 2 short hours Redtail dogs packed 540 bags of food, which equates to 3,780 meals for starving children in Nicaragua!

Our entire session packed enough food for over 35,000 meals, good enough to feed 98 children for a year!

post_text: A BIG thank you to today's helpers at Redtail Ridge! We burned the last big pile of brush while the kids helped haul more up to the fire. We will plan an event in the spring to clean up some more of the path. Thanks again!

post_text: Official Redtail DOGS business cards have been ordered! We should have them in our hands within a week or so. You can pick some up during the DOGS lunch with the kids event on October 3rd or at our DOGS meeting on October 13th.
text: Official Redtail DOGS business cards have been ordered! We should have them in our hands within a week or so. You can pick some up during the DOGS lunch with the kids event on October 3rd or at our DOGS meeting on October 13th.

post_text:
We have secured www.redtaildogs.com which will redirect to this Facebook page for now, but also leaves the door open to create a formal website down the road if needed.

We have also created email forwarding for info@redtaildogs.com which will forward to our redtaildogs@gmail.com email address for now, but again, will also leave the door open for the future.

Note: The redtaildogs.com domain name and email are active, but may take up to 72 hours to populate throughout the internet.

We are also in the process of finalizing our business cards which should be in our hands in the next week or two.

We have a lot of dads that are excited to make a difference this year, so hold on tight because 2014 is going to be a great year to be a DOGS member!

post_text:
Welcome to the new DOGS Facebook page! This will be our new way to communicate to all members. Please feel free to post any comments or pictures you may have as this will also help recruit new members!
Last nights meeting we filled the following positions for our group

President - Jason Wicke
Vice President - Ryan Beaton
Web/IT - Justin Hoveland
PTC Liaison/Treasurer - Mike Harper

We hope this communication system works better and look forward to a great 2014 year!
